From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: mesh-llm <mesh-llm@example.invalid>
Date: Mon, 22 Jun 2026 12:10:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Allocate DSA indexer rotation inputs for GLM_DSA

GLM_DSA now routes normal decode through the DeepSeek32 DSA graph, which
multiplies indexer query/key tensors by the Hadamard rotation input from the
indexer KV cache. The KV cache only forced that rotation input for
DEEPSEEK32, so GLM_DSA could select the DSA graph while failing to allocate
the graph input it requires.

Treat GLM_DSA as a DSA lightning-indexer architecture for this allocation
guard. This is intentionally scoped to cache-input plumbing; GLM-5.2
IndexShare/MTP and layerwise indexer parity remain separate work.
---
 src/llama-kv-cache.cpp | 5 +++--
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/llama-kv-cache.cpp b/src/llama-kv-cache.cpp
index aaa50328f..9d8ee12c5 100644
--- a/src/llama-kv-cache.cpp
+++ b/src/llama-kv-cache.cpp
@@ -337,8 +337,9 @@ llama_kv_cache::llama_kv_cache(
             ggml_is_quantized(type_k) &&
             hparams.n_embd_head_k() % 64 == 0;
 
-        // always create Hadamard rotation tensors for DeepSeek V3.2 DSA lightning indexer
-        if (model.arch == LLM_ARCH_DEEPSEEK32 && hparams.n_embd_head_k_full == hparams.indexer_head_size) {
+        // always create Hadamard rotation tensors for DSA lightning indexer
+        if ((model.arch == LLM_ARCH_DEEPSEEK32 || model.arch == LLM_ARCH_GLM_DSA) &&
+                hparams.n_embd_head_k_full == hparams.indexer_head_size) {
             attn_rot_k = true;
         }
 
